subSubSection.paragraph:
(
Figures 29–31
)

Chaetiger 1 with only a few chaetae on both rami, shorter than chaetae on succeeding chaetigers. Postchaetal lamellae absent on notopodium and auricular on neuropodium, both much smaller than lamellae on succeeding chaetigers (
Fig. 31A
). Prechaetal lamellae absent.

Chaetae from notopodia and neuropodia organized in two rows of wide, unilimbate and granulated capillaries, intensely granulated near base and sparsely granulated near tip (
Fig. 31E
). Notopodial capillaries up to 1.4 times longer than neuropodial capillaries (
Fig. 31F
). Towards end of fragment, capillaries progressively become elongate, non-limbate, non-granulated, thinner and less numerous (
Fig. 31G
).

Hooks in notopodia starting from chaetiger 67, up to three per fascicle, accompanied by 1–4 non-limbate capillaries (
Fig. 31H
). Hooks in neuropodia starting from chaetigers 16–22, up to six per fascicle, accompanied by 1–6 non-limbate capillaries. All hooks multidentate, with 10 secondary teeth arranged in two rows above main tooth (
Figs 30D
; 
31I
). Secondary hood present (
Fig. 31H
). Sabre chaetae starting from chaetigers 14–20. Sabre chaetae non-limbate and intensely granulated throughout length (
Fig. 31J
).
